	<app> <!-- Frustratometer -->
		<name>Frustratometer</name>
		<visible>Yes</visible>
		<desc> <![CDATA[ 
			The Frustratometer is an <a href="frustra_elt.php">Energy Landscape Theory</a> 
			inspired algorithm that aims at quantifying the degree of <a href="frustra_lf.php">
			local frustration</a> manifested in protein molecules. Frustration is a useful concept 
			for gaining insight to the proteins biological behavior by analyzing how the energy is 
			distributed in protein structures and how mutations or conformational changes shift 
			the energy distributions. Sites of high local frustration often indicate biologically 
			important regions such as binding or allosteric sites. Minimally frustrated linkages 
			constitute a stable folding core of the molecule. ]]>		
		</desc>
